i believe - and i shall only pick up on a few ideas - that parliament alone , and no one else , can exert an influence over its members .
if this were not the case , the european parliament ' s authority and representativeness would be seriously undermined in the coming years , and this institution would not move forward , as it should .
it is just as important for no-one to be able to or have to refuse the european parliament or its committees any documentation .
members of parliament must possess the qualities of morality , discipline and discretion over delegated issues innately , and these certainly can not be imposed on them by anyone else .
